abstract: State Department discloses additional 5,500 pages of former Sec of State Hillary Clinton's e-mail messages, but acknowledges failure to meet target set by federal judge of producing 82 percent of documents by end of 2015;  pledges to complete disclosure in early 2016.
lead_paragraph: More messages are disclosed, but officials fail to meet a judge’s requirement to produce 82 percent of her emails by the end of the year.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Steven Lee Myers from Washington, Amy Chozick from New York, and Gardiner Harris from Kailua, Hawaii.

headline.main: More Hillary Clinton Emails Are Released, but State Department Falls Short
headline.print_headline: More Clinton Emails Are Released, but the Target Ordered by a Court Is Not Met
